# Design system

## Tokens (`src/styles/theme.css`)

- Never hardcode visual values: color, radius, typography, shadow, spacing (padding/margin), motion duration/easing, or interaction states.
- Always use CSS custom properties from `src/styles/theme.css`.
- `theme.css` is the only source of design tokens; avoid duplicating hex in TS unless there is a clear need.
- If a needed token does not exist, stop and ask—or request it be added to `theme.css` before continuing.

## Colors — palette only (no semantic tokens)

Use the main palette variables only: `--color-white`, `--color-black`, `--color-accent`, `--color-shade-lightest` through `--color-shade-darkest`.

- Do **not** introduce extra semantic color names (`primary`, `text-muted`, etc.) beyond this palette.
- For icons, pass a palette token to `<Icon color="accent" />` or use `paletteColorVar("accent")` in CSS/`style` — not separate `icon-color-*` utility classes.

### Examples

```css
/* Bad */
.card {
  padding: 16px;
  color: #333;
}

/* Good */
.card {
  padding: var(--space-16);
  color: var(--color-shade-darkest);
}
```

## Motion

- Prefer token-based CSS transitions for simple states (hover, focus, opacity).
- Use [Motion](https://motion.dev) only when it clearly fits: layout transitions, orchestrated sequences, gestures, or motion that is awkward in CSS alone.
- Do not use Motion for every hover or micro-interaction; use CSS + tokens first.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` when adding non-trivial animation.

## Assets and icons

- Do not import, create, or substitute icons/images (no icon packs, no AI placeholders).
- Reference only assets documented in `docs/assets.md` and provided by the owner.
- If an asset is missing, ask for it to be uploaded first.
